subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Size average for the genus (
Fig. 3
). Coloration yellow to golden brown. Head vertex (
Fig. 4a
) black, with some yellow to brown patterns, covered with whitish setae. Fastigium black, area posterior to ocelli brown; ocelli rounded, protruding and outlined with black. Scapes and antennae yellow to dark brown with whitish rings widely spaced out. Entire face and mouthparts yellow, without transverse band (
Fig. 4b
); maxillary palpi whitish to yellowsh. Frons with a dark brown marking. Head lateral side yellowish (
Fig. 4c
), area below eyes brown. Dorsal disc of pronotum brown, with dark brown markings. Lateral lobes of pronotum dark brown, covered with short white setae; ventral margin golden brown. Legs brown to dark brown. Fore- and median femora orange brown, covered with dark setae. Hind femora yellowish basally, darker apically, with white markings and longitudinal bands on external face; knees dark brown. Tibiae dark brown, lighter basally. Tarsomeres brown apically, lighter basally. Tarsomeres 
III-1
with 3–10 spines on dorso-external edge. Abdomen orange brown to golden brown, mottled with black markings. Cerci homogenously dark brown, without markings and rings, covered with hairs.
